# Code of Conduct

## Our Pledge
We pledge to make participation in this project a harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of background, identity, or experience.

## Our Standards
- Be respectful and considerate in communication.
- Do not harass, intimidate, or discriminate.
- Provide constructive feedback and assume good intent.

## Enforcement Responsibilities
Project maintainers are responsible for clarifying standards of acceptable behavior and taking action when standards are not met.

## Scope
This Code of Conduct applies to all project spaces, including GitHub issues, pull requests, mailing lists, chat channels, and in-person events related to the project.

## Enforcement
Instances of abusive, harassing, or otherwise unacceptable behavior may be reported by contacting the project maintainers at [MAINTAINER_EMAIL]. Reports will be reviewed and investigated promptly and fairly.

## Enforcement Guidelines
Consequences for unacceptable behavior may include:
- A private warning from maintainers.
- Temporary or permanent removal from project spaces.
- Public or private apologies as appropriate.

## Attribution
This Code of Conduct is adapted from widely used community conduct guidelines and is provided to ensure a welcoming environment for contributors.
